{
  "doc_id": "55842",
  "text": "As in appetitive situations, the importance of the CS location and CS-related activities received little attention in aversive conditioning procedures. The marked facilitation of avoidance learning by separation of stimulus and response, described by [CITATION_1] , remained unnoticed, perhaps because it arrived in a theoretical vacuum. The use of houselight flashes and placing the source of an auditory CS outside the experimental chamber have remained common practices.",
